# Exchange data access

Two separate channels — do not confuse them.

| Channel | Who | Protocol | Purpose |
| ------- | --- | -------- | ------- |
| **UI ↔ server** | Browser ↔ `presentation/` | WebSocket `/ws/*` + static files | All UI data and commands |
| **Server ↔ exchange** | `application/` / `exchanges/` | ccxt.pro `watch_*` (priority), ccxt `fetch_*` / orders (fallback) | Market and account I/O |

**Hard rule**: browser **never** calls exchange REST or internal `/api/*`.  
WS handler receives a command → delegates to `application/*_service` → service uses `watch_*` or `fetch_*` as below.

## Call stack

```text
Browser  --WebSocket-->  presentation/ws/*_handler
                              │
                              ▼
                       application/*_service
                              │
                  ┌───────────┴───────────┐
                  ▼                       ▼
           watch_* (StreamWorker)    fetch_* / set_leverage / create_order
           exchanges/ ccxt.pro       exchanges/ ccxt REST
```

## When to use exchange REST (`fetch_*`, orders)

Use **`watch_*` first**. REST only when:

- the exchange has no matching `watch*` capability, or
- the operation is inherently request/response (set leverage, place/close order, one-shot fee lookup).

| Data / action | WebSocket (priority) | REST fallback (ccxt) | Typical consumer |
| ------------- | -------------------- | -------------------- | ---------------- |
| Ticker / price | `watch_ticker`, `watch_tickers` | `fetch_ticker` | Screener, Opportunity |
| Order book | `watch_order_book` | `fetch_order_book` | Opportunity ladders |
| USDT balance | `watch_balance` | `fetch_balance` | Account / exchange cards |
| Open positions | `watch_positions` | `fetch_positions` | Orders; e.g. MEXC if no watch |
| Funding rate | partial in ticker | `fetch_funding_rate` | Exchange cards, strategy calc |
| Set leverage | — | `set_leverage` | UI cmd → service → REST |
| Place / close order | — | `create_order`, close | Arb open/close/accumulate |
| Markets / fees | one-time at load | `load_markets`, `fetch_trading_fee`, `fetch_symbol_market_info` | Fee display, min/max order volume |
| 24h volume (discovery) | from ticker | `fetch_ticker` quoteVolume | Screener volume filter |

REST timeout: `Settings.ccxt_request_timeout_ms`.  
Reconnect/backoff for streams: `Settings.ws_reconnect_delay_seconds`.

## Presentation layer (not exchange REST)

| Allowed | Forbidden |
| ------- | --------- |
| `GET /`, `StaticFiles` (HTML/CSS/JS) | FastAPI `/api/*` for UI |
| `GET /health` (ops, optional) | `fetch_*` / ccxt in `presentation/` |
| `WebSocket /ws/*` | HTTP calls from `static/js/` to exchange or internal API |

